tweet: The challenge for $WMT will be a cultural shift towards innovation. They got to Fortune #1 by being slow and steady, but the ecosystem today demands hot and fast. They've got the guns to beat $AMZN but they need to be faster to the draw.

name: Noble Hwang
tweet: $WMT already has a significant wallet share of the American consumer. Their core retail business captures the low end of the market and Sam's Club gives them access to the higher end with near parity to Costco (and my parents already defected). Again, more field to play on.

name: Noble Hwang
tweet: Even before things go nuclear, $WMT has more field to play on because you can experience Walmart in real life as opposed to just on a screen. They have greater potential control over customer experience than any website can have (but maybe AR/VR can change that).

name: Noble Hwang
tweet: $WMT has stores within 10 miles of 70% of the US population. If things go nuclear and online grocery is the future, just flip them into fulfillment centers. That's a cost advantage that $AMZN can't easily replicate.
